  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Building Child-Centered Disaster Resilient Communities in Kon Tum Province, Central Highlands, Vietnam</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In its current phase, the project is increasing the resilience and capacities of vulnerable populations (especially children and ethnic minorities) and relevant institutions to better prepare for, mitigate the effects of, and respond to natural disasters. The current phase of the project is targeting 10 communes in 2 districts (Kon Ray and Kon Plong) of Kon Tum Province, in the Central Highlands of Vietnam. By supporting more effective participation of local communities in planning and monitoring processes, the project is facilitating improved engagement between citizens and local authorities that will support a drive for more effective and improved local governance and ensure those local communities&#x2019; experiences and concerns are reflected in Vietnam&#x2019;s National CBDRM Program.</narrative>
  </description>
